The paper discusses a new information-theoretic policy evaluation technique for reinforcement learning, which involves modeling and compression of data. This technique is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
